  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason: The proposed new dwelling would result in the loss of the integral open and spacious character which exists between the semi-detached villas in this section of Beacon Hill. This openness and spaciousness is considered to be an important component of the character and appearance of the area and would be severely compromised as a result of this proposed development. The development is therefore considered to be contrary to policies D1 (Overall design), D4 (Designing in context), D11 (Alterations and extensions), D26 & D27 (Side extensions), ENV 1 ( New development), H10 ( New development),  policy 9 of  Islington’s Draft Core Strategy, Islington’s Urban Design Guidance 2006, Hillmarton conservation guidance note  and PPS 5."
